	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 26th 3:31 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>How to place your 20 bonus points. <br>15 to strength<br>5 to dexterity<br>some people say 5 to wisdom as this is what gives you mana. I believe we are not casters so mana is not that important. Dex and agi however are.&nbsp;&nbsp;I feel applying the points to dex will help get your procable weapons to proc more therefor it is more important, but people will argue that and i welcome it. <br>If you start in Freeport here is a little guide on what to start doing. Right click on your letter and see who you have to give it to. Go to north Freeport to the paladin guild and hand it off you get a sash so your starting ac will be a little higher. At levels 1 &#8211;5 you do not lose exp so when you run out of food die and you get more. Take the book of discord and put it in the bank. I don&#8217;t suggest a paladin for pvp but if you want to save it till you are at a higher level. Then turn it in. kill the bats at the entrance of the west Freeport gate and stack the wings you can sell a stack of wings for 4 to 5 plat, because many people don&#8217;t know you can buy them. Kill some decaying skelts and save the bones you can sell a stack of those for up to 10 plat.  on the bottom floor of the paladin guild near the pool there is a NPC who will give you a quest if you do this when you are between level 1 and 5 you will get exp. He will give you a bag go kill some pirahna&#8217;s and give to him. Once you hit level 5 go to east commons and start killing fire beettles wolfs and decaying skelts. If you get any medium quality or high quality pelts auction them off a high quality bear pelt will go for 25 plat so a wolf  will go for about 15 or so. Once you have some plat saved up buy some banded armor 1 plat per AC.  Unless your on my server then I just give away my old armor to the first new paladin I see.  Once you can get into a Orc group in east commons get the belts and turn them into the Freeport militia captain he is on the balcony. This will hurt your paladin/cleric faction but this is ok. Later you can do more quests to get that back up and the more faction you have now the less your faction will go down with the militia later when you are doing your quests. Plus you will get exp for turning in the belts and I think 2 gold. Once you hit level 9 go buy your spells. <br><br>Courage - HP(20) and AC(3) buff<br>Cure Poison - Cures target of poison effects Flash of Light - Blinds target<br>Minor Heal - Healing spell (10hp)<br>Spook the Dead - Undead only fear <br>True North - Face to the north. <br>Yaulp - Self only combat buff (str 10) (ac 6<br><br>after that go the ruins in east commons and start killing some mobs there if a ghoul pops shout and someone will come and kill it (DO NOT attempt to kill these around level 10 you will die even in a group) let someone around level 20 go kill them. If I am running through EC and see a shout ill even go them. You can stay in EC until level 12. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Celtpirate Waverider<br>34 paladin<br>saryrn-Boche Morte<br>Yoshiro<br>15 cleric<br>saryrn-House of Wargoth</td></tr>
