	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have posted this several times before but will post it again because it is so important. As a Dwarven Paladin it is CRITICAL that you put 5 pts into Agility. You start with an agility of 70.&nbsp;&nbsp;If your agility is below 75, you take a 50 pt AC hit.  That is a HUGE hit, so as a dwarf, make sure you start by putting 5 pts into Agility.<br><br>I also agree that Dex is important for procing weapons.  I disagree though that you should nerf wisdom. I have worked hard on my wisdom, a little on my strength, and find that I have much more mana than most other Paladins, I can cast more, heal more, stun more, etc. So I like my wisdom. Since strength adds very little to overall damage, unless you can REALLY crank it up, you will see very few benefits from adding a few pts to strength. Armor class is more important, IMHO.<br><br>But it all comes down to how you want to play your character.  Buff your strength if you want or buff your wisdom. Play it how you want to...that's what it's all about.<br><br>Kneesmasher Ayebulger<br>34th Circle of Dwarven Paladins<br>Twilight Brethren<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
